# gen180 — B5 recursion / calls: parrot0 evaluates a call inside an expression by
# re-entering the evaluator on the named function (under a recursion-depth
# ceiling), so recursive and helper-calling functions compute. A call to a
# function not present in the snippet is refused honestly.
#expect: pass
#faculty: symeval-recursion
> what does fact(5) return: int fact(int n) { if (n <= 1) { return 1; } return n * fact(n - 1); }
< fact(5) returns 120
> what does fib(10) return: int fib(int n) { if (n < 2) { return n; } return fib(n - 1) + fib(n - 2); }
< fib(10) returns 55
> what does f(5) return: int dbl(int x) { return x * 2; } int f(int n) { return dbl(n) + 1; }
< f(5) returns 11
